a variable can't start with an integer or a pyhton word like if, for, etc. 
a variable can't have any symbol like -,#,@ etc.
it can only start with either a letter or an underscore 
Operators : +,-,*,/,//,%,**
in an expression say 18+5 '+' is an operator and 18,5 are operands
+=concatenate
-=subtracts
*=multiplies
/=division giving you the exact result as a real number. eg : 34/5 = 6.8
